{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Context-aware insert/remove toggle at the mouse cursor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Audio item: insert or remove a stretch marker\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MIDI item: insert or remove a rated take marker (1.00x)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ruler / empty area: insert or remove a tempo+time-signature marker\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Settings are read from REAPER ExtState section "konst_InsertAtMouse". You can configure them in konst_Import MusicXML (Settings > Insert at Mouse).\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55356 ?\u57272 ? MusicXML Tools for REAPER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script imports and exports {\b MusicXML} files directly inside REAPER while preserving guitar-specific information such as {\b string and fret positions}, articulations, and track structure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It was originally designed to work seamlessly with {\b ReaTab Hero}, eliminating the need to manually reassign strings and frets after exporting MIDI from notation software like Guitar Pro. The script has since grown into a more complete {\b MusicXML workflow tool for REAPER}, supporting both import and export, articulation editing, and flexible project integration.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MusicXML Import\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Parses {\f1 <string>} and {\f1 <fret>} elements and maps string numbers to MIDI channels (string 1 \u8594 ? channel 7, etc.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Preserves guitar articulation information such as slides, hammer-ons, vibrato, harmonics, bends, mutes, and more\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Converts articulations into {\b text events, markers, or cue events} (fully configurable)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Handles {\b drum parts} with configurable per-family MIDI channel mapping\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Expands repeat sections (forward/backward repeats)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Supports chord offsets and complex rhythmic structures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optional {\b tempo and time signature import}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MusicXML Export\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Export selected {\b MIDI items back to MusicXML}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Preserves:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab measures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab staff grouping\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab notes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab articulations\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Supports {\b key signatures via REAPER KSIG notation events}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Includes a small UI to quickly set key signatures before export\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Preserves {\b MIDI bank/program data} (Bank Select MSB/LSB + Program Change)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Track & Project Integration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Creates separate MIDI tracks for each staff\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Three insertion modes:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Create new tracks} \u8211- original behavior\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Insert on existing tracks} \u8211- places MIDI items on selected tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Match tracks by name} \u8211- automatically maps staves to existing tracks\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Stores {\b string tuning as track ExtState} for compatibility with ReaTab Hero\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Articulation Workflow\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fully configurable articulation system\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each articulation can define:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab symbol text\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab event type (Text / Marker / Cue)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab fret replacement behavior\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab enable/disable toggle\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Click articulation labels in settings to {\b insert articulation text events directly on selected MIDI notes}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Alt + Click} removes articulation events\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 User Interface & Workflow\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dedicated GUI with organized settings sections:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab GENERAL\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab IMPORT\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab EXPORT\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab ARTICULATION\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Drag & drop MusicXML files directly onto the script window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Custom dark-themed UI elements:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab scrollable menus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab message boxes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab unified scrollbars\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dockable window (top / bottom / left / right)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optional {\b stay-on-top mode}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optional {\b auto-focus on mouse hover}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Font selection for the UI\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Window position memory\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Default / last path handling for file browsing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Open exported file or folder automatically after export\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Via ReaPack (recommended)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab In REAPER open {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Import Repositories}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Paste the repository link\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kkonstantin2000/konst_reascripts/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Click {\b OK}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Run {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Synchronize packages}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Install:\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Script: konst_Import MusicXML.lua\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Manual Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Download:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 konst_Import MusicXML.lua\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 from the repository and place it in your {\b REAPER Scripts} directory, then load it via the {\b Action List}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Run the script from the {\b Action List}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Select an uncompressed {\b MusicXML (.xml)} file\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Choose import settings (tempo markers, articulation behavior, etc.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Import the file\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script will create MIDI items containing notes, string channel information, and articulation events.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For best results with {\b ReaTab Hero}, ensure the target track has the correct tuning. The script can automatically store tuning data as {\b track ExtState}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Feedback & Contributions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you encounter a bug or have a feature request:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Open an issue on GitHub\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Or post in the REAPER forum thread\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=307042"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=307042
}}}
\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Credits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thanks to {\b ExtremRaym} for creating {\b ReaTab Hero} and for helpful feedback during development.\par}
}
